1. Install Kubectl
https://docs.aws.amazon.com/eks/latest/userguide/install-kubectl.html

2. IAM Role with AmazonEKSClusterPolicy to create eks cluster

3. install update aws cli 
https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/getting-started-install.html

4. Install or update eksctl 
https://eksctl.io/installation/

5. Create eks cluster https://docs.aws.amazon.com/eks/latest/userguide/create-cluster.html

6. aws eks update-kubeconfig --region region-code --name my-cluster [to update profile in your cluster]

7. For creating worker node it should have  an iam role having "Amazoneksworkernodeploicy" and amazonec2conatinerregistryreadonlypolicy

